A customer reported that when trying to build the FishEye plugin version 3.0.10 off the tag, he could not obtain the correct version of this dependency from our maven repo: {{jira-subproject-plugins}}

bq. Also, I just tried to build the jira-fisheye-plugin-3.0.10 tag, which has the jira dependency set to 4.0.0-RC1. This caused a build failure because https://maven.atlassian.com/repository/public/com/atlassian/jira/jira-subproject-plugins/4.0.0-RC1 does not exist. I then tried setting the jira version to 4.0, but this had missing deps as well. I finally got it to build with 4.0.0-Beta5. Just FYI.

It seems that the only version of that dep we have published is for 4.0.0-Beta5.

We should investigate why we are not publishing this for all released versions, or even if we should be publishing this at all.

As to the question of why the FishEye plugin depends on this dep at all, this is what TimP had to say:

{quote}
jira-subproject-plugins is the parent pom for the rest plugin, which is a dependant plugin of the fisheye plugin
so it should be deployed publicly if users want to be depend on the rest plugin (ie. to be able to deploy their own REST end points)
which the FishEye plugin does for it's gadgets
{quote}

