When you click on the Popular Issues view into a project, it's great to be able to see how many people have voted on each issue, what the status of the issue is, what type of issue it is, etc.

I think additionally fundamental statistics are whether an issue has ever been assigned to anyone to resolve and how many years / months / weeks / days an issue has been open.

When trying to decide, for example, whether to use a particular open source package, if you see that its 5 most popular issues have been open for 5 years or longer and have never been assigned to anyone, you can use that as a data point in your decision making process.

